the courtordered removal of children from the 
bethel home for children due to suspicion of brutality and neglect 
infuriated founder herman fountain who bitterly regretted his 
failure to defy authorities in the name of church rights before 
the battle of bethel was over he would have another chance to do 
just that this is the third and concluding installment of gates 
of hell 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
fridays raid at the bethel home for 
children was followed by mondays last stand 
over the weekend word reached judge robert oswald that some of 
the children who had fled police had returned to bethel he ordered 
authorities back to the church to retrieve any children they could 
find 
bethel founder herman fountain in youth court awaiting further 
hearing testimony caught wind of the action and ordered his staff 
to ignore the subpoenas that had summoned them and return to 
bethel there would be no compromise on this day 
fountain locked the church doors barricading three dozen 
parents and children in the church they had built by hand dozens 
of state troopers and sheriffs deputies stood by for more than 
three hours while welfare commissioner thomas brittain jr tried 
to negotiate the childrens release 
police finally broke in and took the children while church 
members recited bible verse and sang hymns 
if god be for us who can be against us read the bethel sign 
by the road 
fountain his eldest son herman jr nicknamed bubba and 
brother david owens were among eight people arrested that day 
fountain faces three counts of felonious assault on a police 
officer and one count of inciting a riot all scheduled to be 
presented to the grand jury later this month 
troubles seemed to overrun the pastor like the locusts of 
pharaohs egypt a former bethel resident rhonnda traxler 
gathered reporters outside the courthouse and alleged fountain 
sexually molested her and another girl while they were at bethel 
fountain denied the accusation and leveled his own you cant 
believe this girl theres no telling how many men shes been 
with 
another former bethel child ray friery filed a 1 million 
federal lawsuit against fountain alleging assault and battery 
abuse neglect and false imprisonment 
fountain wasnt the only one with problems many state workers 
involved in the case received harassing phone calls or believed 
they were being followed by bethel supporters 
brittain sent his 13yearold daughter out of state after 
anonymous callers threatened to kidnap her and put her in a church 
home where she would never be found again 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
before the youth court hearings ended about half of the more 
than 70 children taken from bethel had testified some were too 
frightened to appear 
theyre really wicked little kids fountain said in a later 
interview with the associated press im talking about 
homosexuals im talking about lesbians im talking about 
prostitutes im talking about one boy who raped his 84yearold 
grandmother im talking about one who murdered his sister 
im talking habitual runaways im talking car thieves im 
talking nymphomaniacs 
brittain dealt with the same youngsters but saw something 
different 
for the most part theyre pretty normal kids who have been 
battered around by life pretty badly the welfare commissioner 
said theyre children trying to put their lives back together 
some parents had despaired of getting help from state agencies 
for them bethel was a last resort for others it was a matter of 
convenience one child was sent to bethel because he took food 
from the refrigerator brittain said 
but as the hearing continued after the raid on bethel some 
parents sat in the courtroom and wept overwhelmed by stories of 
hairpulling faceslapping laprunning and switchings a 
13yearold girl with downs syndrome said she ran laps all day 
long received frequent spankings and sometimes stood for hours on 
tiptoe with her chin above a light switch 
they said she was a little brat and had a demon in her 
another girl said parents agreed with it they said thats what 
you deserve if youve acted in a wrong way 
some parents said they were misled they didnt know what bethel 
really was other parents knew exactly what bethel was 
when i went down there i was totally convinced what had 
occurred was not morally right legally right or anyway right 
said jack hicks of birdsboro pa but his two teenage sons support 
fountain and they changed his mind 
