for two months in the summer of 1968 the 
student movement gained momentum mexico liberty they 
shouted on oct 2 army machine guns silenced them 10 days before 
the citys olympic games 
that night the night of tlatelolco was one of the bloodiest 
ends to the protests that shook the world in 1968 officials put 
the death toll at 29 but students said hundreds were killed 
the movement withered and seemed to die but 20 years later 
festering discontent with a political system governed by a single 
party reemerged in an unprecedented vote against the stilldominant 
institutional revolutionary party or pri 
at the very high price of lives of blood of prison for many 
people the 68 movement opened a democratic channel that kept 
swelling until it overflowed in 1988 said gilberto guevara one 
of the principal leaders of the movement 
in the july 1988 general elections the opposition made 
unprecedented gains in parliament against the pri in power since 
1929 
mexico in 1968 was still in its miracle years of economic 
expansion the authoritarian government dominated unions campesino 
organizations and the press 
despite the growth distances between the classes also were 
growing and that wasnt the heritage expected of a government that 
