<TEXT>
the supreme court today turned away arguments 
that the policies of the bonneville power administration are 
costing electricity consumers in california billions of dollars 
the justices without comment decided not to order changes in 
the way the bpa distributes hydroelectric power throughout the 
pacific northwest and california 
the bpa an independent selffinanced marketer of electric 
power within the federal department of energy sells electricity 
generated by 31 federal dams in the pacific northwest it also 
operates a system of electric power transmission lines 
the legal controversy acted on today involves the transmission 
line system which is called the pacific northwestpacific 
southwest intertie 
congress established the system in the late 1960s in order for 
the pacific northwest and pacific southwest to exchange power when 
one region has a surplus supply and the other region has a heavy 
demand 
bpa owns and operates most of the intertie transmission lines 
north of the oregoncalifornia border lines south of that boundary 
are owned by several california utilities 
bpa policies on distribution of power over the transmission 
lines were challenged in a lawsuit by the two california state 
agencies the public utilities commission and the energy resources 
conservation and development commission 
the agencies contended that the bpa access policies illegally 
excluded lowcost energy generated in the pacific northwest and 
canada from the transmission system the state agencies said 
lowercost energy thus was prevented from reaching california 
consumers 
the 9th us circuit court of appeals ruled for the bpa last 
november 
in seeking the supreme courts help lawyers for the california 
agencies said the transmission line access policy will produce a 
transfer of wealth between regions of the united states on the 
order of billions of dollars 
reagan administration lawyers urged the justices to reject the 
appeals 
the cases are california energy resources conservation and 
development commission vs bpa 871835 and california puc vs 
bpa 871836 
</TEXT>
