competent to decide on making appeals 
the execution was scheduled to be carried out at one minute 
after midnight so that if it was blocked prosecutors would have 
more than 23 hours under the tuesday death warrant to try to have 
the stay lifted 
authorities at the missouri state penitentiary proceeded monday 
as though the execution would take place said spokesman dale riley 
in their order staying the execution the three judges said more 
time was needed to review an affidavit from a psychiatrist 
questioning whether smith was competent to make decisions on his 
fate 
in an interview friday at the prison smith said he considers 
all further appeals hopeless and criticized outside efforts to stop 
the execution 
asked how he would react if a court stepped in and blocked it 
smith said they can only block it for so long everythings been 
resolved theyre going over the same things because they have 
nothing else to go over 
smith complained friday about the public defender appeal saying 
it inaccurately said his wife had influenced him to drop appeals 
smith ruled competent by a federal judge two years ago said he 
had made the decision before he met his wife whom he married in 
prison last year 
smith was convicted of using an eightpound iron bar to beat to 
death karen roberts a woman he said had given him a venereal 
disease and caused him to lose his fiancee he was given a second 
death penalty for his part in the 1985 stabbing murder of fellow 
death row inmate robert baker 
the states emergency motion filed in response to the stay noted 
that last week a different threejudge panel of the 8th circuit 
had refused to block the execution 
the panel should not allow such a collateral attack upon their 
opinion the states motion said 
gov john ashcroft issued a statement saying that a review of 
smiths record by the state board of probation and parole provided 
no new information that would prompt him to step in and block the 
execution 
