of handing back new chiado apartments to the areas preblaze 
residents who benefited from longstanding rent control 
new apartments on expensive city center ground mean new leases 
and higher rents forcing former lowincome residents out of a new 
residential chiado the fire rendered 300 people homeless and left 
1200 shopworkers unemployed two people were killed in the fire 
and 43 were injured 
