guilty to accepting 6000 in bribes and was sentenced to eight 
years in prison in may 1987 
he presided over a smelly cramped courtroom on the 11th floor 
above police headquarters on the citys south side that became in 
the words of the federal judge who sentenced him a cesspool of 
corruption 
