<TEXT>
seventeen americans served as state or 
territorial governors before becoming president although most also 
held senior elected or appointed federal office before winning the 
white house 
the two most recent exceptions are jimmy carter and ronald 
reagan michael dukakis hopes to become a third 
the list of former governors who became president includes some 
of the most distinguished chief executives and some who are 
scarcely remembered 
thomas jefferson who was governor of virginia during the 
american revolution tops the list jefferson the third president 
doubled the size of the nation by purchasing the louisiana 
territory from france in 1803 
he had some training along the way being principle author of 
the declaration of independence negotiating the peace treaty with 
great britain then serving as ambassador to france and secretary 
of state 
james monroe another virginia governor became the fifth 
president after serving in the us senate as envoy to france 
britain and spain and as secretary of war and state 
andrew jackson was territorial governor of florida four years 
after defeating the seminole indians in that state 
his successor martin van buren was governor of new york after 
serving in the us senate and was jacksons secretary of state 
and vice president 
other 19th century presidents who had been governors include 
william henry harrison of indiana john tyler of virginia james 
knox polk and andrew johnson of tennessee rutherford b hayes of 
ohio and grover cleveland of new york 
william mckinley the 25th president was governor of ohio for 
189296 
theodore roosevelt who was vice president and took office after 
mckinleys assassination had been assistant navy secretary before 
resigning in 1897 to organize the rough riders in the 
spanishamerican war he was governor of new york for 18991901 
woodrow wilson who had graduate degrees in law and political 
science was president of princeton university before serving as 
governor of new jersey in 191113 he was elected president in 1912 
and invaded mexico in 1914 the year that world war i began in 
europe he was reelected in 1916 with the slogan he kept us out 
of war but declared war on germany the following year 
calvin coolidge served as governor of massachusetts for 191920 
and for 192123 was vice president to warren harding who died in 
office 
franklin delano roosevelt was governor of new york for 192933 
after serving as assistant navy secretary in 191320 a post which 
deeply involved him in diplomacy and logistics in world war i and 
prepared him for his leadership role in world war ii 
jimmy carter served for one term as governor of georgia before 
his election as president in 1976 
ronald reagan a twoterm california governor defeated carter 
in 1980 
