j ralph corbett founder of nutone co a 
pioneer in the manufacture of home door chimes and a noted patron 
of the arts died monday at a cincinnati retirement community he 
was 91 
corbett founded nutone an electrical manufacturing company in 
cincinnati in 1936 the company considered the worlds largest 
maker of home door chimes was sold in 1967 to scovill 
manufacturing co of waterbury conn 
corbett also established the corbett foundation which since its 
founding in 1955 has given almost 30 million to the arts 
corbett was born dec 5 1896 in the flushing section of the 
new york city borough of queens he married patricia barry a 
radiotelevision singer and long island native on july 23 1930 
he received a bachelor of law degree at the new york university 
law school in 1923 corbett began his business career in new york 
city as a marketing consultant and adviser to manufacturers and 
financial organizations in the east and moved to cincinnati in 
1933 
survivors include his wife patricia a daughter a son and a 
grandson 
a memorial sevice is scheduled for oct 18 at the university of 
cincinnati collegeconservatory of music 
